# Zhuotuan Backend Development Skill

Use this project workflow when extending the backend:

1. Read the relevant `docs/backend_plan/modules/*.md` file before editing code.
2. Prefer script-first validation over API-first delivery; only wrap stable flows in FastAPI.
3. Treat LLM output as untrusted: update prompt, normalizer, schema, validator and tests together.
4. Generate ids in backend code, never rely on LLM-generated ids or generated artifacts as a fix.
5. Do not patch test artifacts to hide generation bugs; fix prompt and post-processing instead.
6. Keep world, module and character steps independently runnable and debuggable.
7. For character cards, validate against world-defined attributes, world-defined skills and module roster constraints.
8. Keep skills world-driven: values are `0=不会`, `1=会`, `2=精通`, and total points must fit the world budget.
9. After behavior changes, update README commands and the relevant docs in the same change.
10. Run unit tests first, then integration/golden tests when schemas or artifacts changed.
